Government needs to earn respect by convincing people to do what they ask through non-violent non-coercive means. The only time the government is allowed to use force or jail anyone is when that individual physically harms someone else or their property. All other cases are a matter of free will. If someone does something to indirectly harm you, typically financially or physically through methods such as a bad product or through indirect means such as pollution or otherwise, only then should civil liability play a roll. What you say and how you express yourself should not be punished legally speaking. Physically Harming someone else is the only preclusion on any free speech you might have, but then it is a matter of direct harm that can be traced back directly to your actions that you should be punished for, rather then some nebulous issue with process or otherwise. What you say and do always has social consequences, lying under oath has significant reputational harm that should be preferenced over any "jail time" for such actions.
